{{distinguish|Anti-sexism}} {{Refimprove|date=September 2011}} '''Antisexualism''' is opposition or hostility towards [[Human sexual activity|sexual behavior]] and [[Human sexuality|sexuality]].<ref>{{citation |title=The politics of lust |author=John Ince |page=11 |publisher=Prometheus Books |quote=consists of any negative response directed at sex organs or harmless sex expression |isbn=978-1-59102-278-7 |year=2005}}</ref>
==Terminology== Other terms whose meanings overlap or are synonymous or interchangeable with antisexualism include ''sex-negativism'',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.philadelphiaweekly.com/columns/philly-collective-talks-sex-positive-resistance-in-american-politics/article_ecb55b3a-399b-11e7-971c-1fbc9b45af1c.html|title=Philly collective talks sex-positive resistance in American politics|first=Timaree|last=Schmit|publisher=}}</ref> ''[[sex-negative]] movement'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newstatesman.com/politics/health/2016/08/hiv-drug-dispute-highlights-danger-conservative-case-gay-rights|title=The HIV drug dispute highlights the danger of the conservative case for gay rights|website=www.newstatesman.com}}</ref> ''sex-negativity'',<ref>Rubin, Gayle. "Thinking sex: Notes for a radical theory of the politics of sexuality." Social Perspectives in Lesbian and Gay Studies; A Reader (1984): 100-133.</ref> ''antisexuality'',<ref>Berer, Marge. "Sexuality, rights and social justice." Reproductive Health Matters 12.23 (2004): 6-11.</ref> ''demonization of sex''<ref>Dillon, M. C. "Sex objects and sexual objectification: Erotic versus pornographic depiction." Journal of Phenomenological Psychology 29.1 (1998): 92-115.</ref> or as an adjective, ''anti-sex'' or ''sex-negative''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/joe-barton-sex-scandal_us_5a1d8e2fe4b06a14100a563f|title=Another GOP Lawmaker Got Caught In A Sex Scandal. Here's Why You Should Defend Him.|date=29 November 2017|publisher=}}</ref><ref>Shrage, Laurie. "Exposing the fallacies of anti-porn feminism." Feminist Theory 6.1 (2005): 45-65.</ref> In a broader scope, it may refer to a general opposition to sexuality,<ref>{{cite web| title= Definition of “antisexuality” |work= |date= |publisher=[[Collins English Dictionary]] |accessdate= March 12, 2013 |url= http://www.collinsdictionary.com/dictionary/english/antisexuality }}</ref> especially tending to reduce or eliminate the [[sex drive]] or sexual activity<ref>{{cite web| title= Definition of ANTISEX |work= |date= |publisher=[[Merriam-Webster]] |accessdate=March 12, 2013 |url= http://www.merriam-webster.com/medical/antisex }}</ref> or a prudish and coitophobic force in society that suppress sexual freedom and disseminate antisexual opinions.<ref>{{cite book | last = Gescinska | first = Alicja A. | editor1-last = Clarke | editor1-first = Gemma | editor2-last = McQueen | editor2-first = Fiona | editor3-last = Pnacekova | editor3-first = Michaela | editor4-last = Sahli | editor4-first = Sabrina | title = Examining aspects of sexualities and the self | url = http://hdl.handle.net/1854/LU-924760 | accessdate = March 12, 2013 | type = Conference | series = Critical Issues | volume = 121 | year = 2010 | publisher = [[Inter-Disciplinary Press]] | location = Oxford, UK | isbn = 978-1-84888-020-7 | id = 924760 | pages = 87–94 | chapter = Sex in transition: anti-sexuality and the church in post-communist Poland | chapterurl = https://biblio.ugent.be/publication/924760/file/2093524.pdf | postscript = &nbsp;&nbsp;6th Global Conference : Sexualities : Bodies, Desires, Practices }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.pseudology.org/Kon/English/Sexual%20counter-revolution%20in%20Russia.htm |title= Sexual culture and politics in contemporary Russia |first= Igor S. |last= Kon |authorlink= Igor S. Kon |date= |month= |year= |work= Sexual counter-revolution in Russia |publisher= Fatekh Vergasov’s electronic library |location= Russia |accessdate= 2013-03-12 |quote= The current anti-sexual crusade is only the top of the iceberg. Under the guise of a moral renaissance, [[Russian Orthodox Church|Russian Orthodoxy]] and its allies are trying to restore [[Censorship in Russia|censorship]] and administrative control over private life. |postscript=}}</ref> When such an aversion involves hatred it is sometimes termed miserotia or miserotism.<ref>Houdini, I. V., and X. Merlin. "Of Sex and Fear." Word Ways 7.2 (1974): 19.</ref>
==Religious== Some forms of early ascetic [[Gnosticism]] held all matter to be evil, and that unnecessary gratifications of the physical senses were to be avoided. Married couples were encouraged to be chaste.<ref>{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=hBJ-KZU_XE4C&pg=PT47|title=Why You Think the Way You Do: The Story of Western Worldviews from Rome to Home|last=Sunshine|first=Glenn S.|page=47|publisher=[[Zondervan]]|year=2009|isbn=9780310292302|accessdate=2013-08-31}}</ref><ref>See [[Book of Thomas the Contender]], [[Acts of Thomas]]; also [[Spiritual marriage]]</ref> The [[Skoptsy]]s were a radical sect of the [[Russian Orthodox Church]] that practiced [[castration]] and amputation of sexual organs. The Skoptsy believed that Christ had been castrated during his crucifixion, and it was this castration that brought about salvation.<ref>{{cite book|title=A Mind of Its Own: A Cultural History of the Penis|last=Friedman|first=David M.|publisher=[[Simon & Schuster]]|year=2008|isbn=9781439136089|pages=36–37|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dYYx-sHniI8C&pg=PA36|accessdate=2013-08-31}}</ref> [[Boston Corbett]], who was involved in killing John Wilkes Booth, castrated himself after being mocked and tempted by prostitutes.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.kansas.com/2013/02/10/2671375/thomas-corbett-moved-to-kansas.html|title=Boston Corbett moved to Kansas after John Wilkes Booth shooting|last=Tanner|first=Beccy|date=2013-02-11|work=[[The Wichita Eagle]]|accessdate=2013-08-31}}</ref> [[Ann Lee]] was the founder of the [[Shakers]], a radical [[Protestant]] sect that opposed procreation and all sexual activity. The Shakers were more opposed to pregnancy than anything else.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.newyorker.com/archive/2006/02/13/060213crat_atlarge|title=Shining Tree of Life|first=Adam|last=Gopnik|work=[[The New Yorker]]|date=2006-02-13|accessdate=2013-08-31}}</ref>{{better source needed|date=June 2018|reason=This is not apparent from Shaker primary sources. Find a specialized work on the topic.}} [[Father Divine]], founder of the International Peace Mission Movement, advocated religious abstinence from sex and marriage and taught that sexual objectification is a root cause of undesirable social and political conditions.<ref>{{cite book |last1=Watts |first1=Jill |date= |year=1992 |title=God, Harlem U.S.A.: The Father Divine Story |trans-title= |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=hRKCcyndVvkC |access-date=12 February 2017|dead-url= |format= |language=English |location= |publisher=University of California Press |page=66 |isbn= |via= |subscription= |quote=All disciples subscribed to Father Divine's teaching that sex was a sin that drained the body of "spiritual energy", making the individual vulnerable to disease and death. Even followers who lived outside 72 Macon Street practiced celibacy. |trans-quote=}}</ref>
==Anaphrodisiacs== [[John Harvey Kellogg]], the inventor of the "corn flakes" variety of breakfast cereal, was opposed to all forms of sexual activity, especially [[masturbation]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.villagevoice.com/2004-05-11/columns/come-for-a-cause/|first=Tristan|last=Taormino|title=Come for a Cause|work=[[The Village Voice]]|date=2004-05-11|accessdate=2013-08-31}}</ref> ''[[The Road to Wellville]]'' satirized his life and practices.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.deseretnews.com/article/700001548/Road-to-Wellville-The.html?pg=all|first=Chris|last=Hicks|date=1994-11-01|title=Film review: Road to Wellville, The|work=[[Deseret News]]|accessdate=2013-08-31}}</ref> According to some sources, the early Christian theologian [[Origen]] castrated himself to avoid temptation and remain pure.<ref>{{cite news|title=The Way of All Flesh|last=Rothwell|first=Nicholas|url=http://www.theaustralian.com.au/arts/books/the-way-of-all-flesh/story-e6frg8nf-1111117239747|date=2008-08-23|work=[[The Australian]]|accessdate=2013-08-31}}</ref>
==Movements== {{original research|section|date=August 2013}}
The most popular venue of antisexuals is the Antisex.info (Antisexual Stronghold) website founded by [[Yuri Leonidovich Nesterenko|Yuri Nesterenko]].<ref name="Чудакова">{{cite web |url= http://www.interfax.ru/russia/txt.asp?id=20397 |script-title=ru:Против секса |first= Алиса |last= Чудакова |date= July 7, 2008 |work= |publisher= [[Interfax]] |location= |language= Russian |trans-title=|accessdate= 2013-02-20 |quote= }}</ref> He has been widely recognized as the leading antisexual activist since he launched a [[FidoNet]]-based antisexual community in 1995.<ref name="Чудакова"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mk.ru/editions/atmosphere/article/2007/11/08/71125-zhizn-bez-seksa.html |script-title=ru:Жизнь без секса |first=Татьяна |last=Арефьева |date=November 8, 2007 |publisher=[[Moskovskij Komsomolets|Атмосфера]] № 67 |language=Russian |trans-title=Life without sex |accessdate=2013-02-21 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140301083100/http://www.mk.ru/editions/atmosphere/article/2007/11/08/71125-zhizn-bez-seksa.html |archivedate=2014-03-01 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.segodnya.ua/oldarchive/c2256713004f33f5c2256cba00413266.html |script-title=ru:Жизнь без секса |author= An anonymous author |date= 2003-01-27 |work= |publisher= [[Segodnya|Газета «Сегодня»]], Выпуск №19 (1364) |language= Russian |trans-title=Life without sex |accessdate= 2013-02-21 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|date=May–June 2006 |script-title=ru:Мы не спустим! |journal=[[:fr:Moulin rouge (magazine)|Moulin rouge]] |location=[[Moscow]] |publisher=[[Rodionov Publishing House]] |language=Russian |accessdate=2013-02-22 |url=http://moulin-rouge.telion.ru/2006/05/140/1 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140302205455/http://moulin-rouge.telion.ru/2006/05/140/1 |archivedate=2014-03-02 |df= }}</ref><ref name=antisex>{{ru icon}} [http://video.yandex.ru/users/sharnion/view/8/# Теория невероятности. Жизнь без секса] (a documentary)</ref><ref>{{cite journal | last =